Meet the 2023 Hot Wheels Legends Tour Global Finale Winner: Chris Watson, with his 1990 Mazda MX-5 roadster (aka The CHIMERA).
�Hailing all the way from New Zealand, the CHIMERA will now be immortalized as a Hot Wheels Legend at 1:64 scale and sold around the world.

After battling it out for the top spot, our judges agreed it checked all the boxes:

✅ Creativity
✅ Authenticity
✅ Garage Spirit

Are you looking forward to adding this Legend to your Hot Wheels collection? Let us know!

text:
The Texas Toot took the crown and crushed the competition during the 2022 Hot Wheels Legends Tour and we’ve turned this winner into a 1:64 scale die-cast.

Here’s your first look at the Mazda Autozam, available for purchase Spring 2024.

text:
Join us for the EPIC FINALE of the Hot Wheels Legends Tour to find out who will get their car made into a Hot Wheels die-cast toy car! The excitement of the annual Hot Wheels Legends Tour Presented by Mobil 1, our international search for the next custom ride to make into a Hot Wheels die-cast.
Watch LIVE judging from a panel of celebrities and automotive legends, including Noel Gugliemi, Jay Leno, Dalal Elsheikh, Larry Chen, Toni Breidinger and the Hot Wheels design team.
The Hot Wheels Legends Tour is made possible in partnership with Walmart and Presenting Sponsor, Mobil 1.
Learn more about the Hot Wheels Legends Tour at www.hotwheels.com/legends

text:
Join us for the Semi-Finals of the Hot Wheels Legends Tour! Watch LIVE judging from a panel of celebrities and top motorsport athletes, including Coco Zurita, Aimee Shackelford, and Eric Kendricks
The Hot Wheels Legends Tour, now in its sixth year, is a global search for the next fan-made custom car to be made into a Hot Wheels die-cast.

The Hot Wheels Legends Tour is made possible in partnership with Walmart and Presenting Sponsor, Mobil 1.
Learn more about the Hot Wheels Legends Tour at www.hotwheels.com/legends

text:
🏆 Your finalist of the Hawaii stop of the Hot Wheels Legends Tour 🌺🏁🚗

Check out this '69 Camaro with a 6.2 LS engine, stock bottom end, custom turbo hot side & cool side (all TIG welded by the owner), and a beastly 92mm turbo. This street-legal small tire car blazes through the quarter mile in just 8.77 seconds. Every detail, from beadrolling the aluminum parts to building the engine and porting the heads, was done by the owner himself. Legends are made, not born, and this Camaro is proof of that! 🚀💨

text:
ARTFUL RELICS

Aged, eroded, but ultimately unbroken. Our Hot Wheels x Daniel Arsham collab begins with the decayed Super Rally Case featuring a frosted back and rubble-inspired shelves. Start filling it with the 1:64 version of Arsham’s Porsche 930 sculpture and the Eroded Rodger Dodger.

"To give the vehicles a premium feel, we turned to Silkstone, a modern material that has a porcelain appearance and a heavier, more tactile feel than plastic. It allows for more sharpness and details than die-cast metal." - Ethan Wood, Senior Director of Design

Get these Mattel Creations collectibles on October 27 at MattelCreations.com at 9 AM PT or IRL October 21-October 22 at our Hot Wheels x Daniel Arsham NYC Celebration.

text:
Meet Rampy, the latest finalist on the Hot Wheels Legends Tour. Built by the automotive virtuoso Wayne Dick! 🚗💨 It took 2 years and a whopping 790 hours of fabrication to create this automotive masterpiece. With a 6.2L engine, BTR stage 3 cam, and 420HP on the wheels, it's pure power on four wheels. Featuring C5 suspension, Air Rex struts, Acuair air management system, and Weld wheels, this ride is a work of art on wheels. 🛠️

Starting as a bone-stock truck, it's been transformed into a speed demon with heart and soul. Rampy's journey includes an 11.89-second quarter-mile run at 110mph, conquering autocross, and cruising 20k miles in just 18 months.

But Rampy's true mission? To drive, have fun, and bring smiles to people's faces everywhere it goes. 🤩🙌 Congratulations to Wayne and Rampy on taking the El Segundo Hot Wheels Legends Tour finalist spot!

Cruising into the Hot Wheels Legends Tour semi-finals is the Isetta dream team: 'Big Dill' and 'The Pickle Jar' 🥒 Congratulations @mikeybrown1957!

Under the hood, 'Big Dill' packs a punch with a custom-built 1.2-liter V-twin motorcycle engine sourced from Harley-Davidson, replacing the original single-cylinder engine. 🔧 And 'The Pickle Jar'? Well, it's not your typical flatbed hauler featuring Model A fenders that add flair to the rear, while the front gets a character look with Volkswagen Beetle fenders and lights. 🚚✨

Do you think Mikey's builds have what it takes to bring home the ultimate prize? Let us know!

text:
This was the BIGGEST Hot Wheels UK Legends tour ever, but who won?

Watch the highlights now and visit https://bitly.ws/WsIf to find out more about the competition.

The 2023 Hot Wheels Legends Tour UK saw over 250 entries vying to represent the UK in a global search for the next Hot Wheels Legend.

Ten UK finalists came together at RADwood on 9/2 to be judged on 'authenticity, creativity and garage spirit' by an expert team from the world of motoring - including Hot Wheels designer Craig Callum and led by classic car whiz Paul Cowland.

From a 700bhp Ford Transit to a race-ready Skoda 130, a huge variety of vehicles made it to the UK final, with the winner now facing the Legends Tour Semi-Final in a bid to make it through to the Global Finale and be in with a shot at the overall prize – joining the 2 Jet Z, the NASH, and the UK's own Volvo P1800 Gasser in the hallowed Hot Wheels Garage of Legends.”
